close_reason: "Addressed Greptile and CodeRabbit claim-next contract, author, XOR, and completion findings with full coverage."
body: "## Context\nSplit out of pm-8t5x (claim test-and-set): once claim correctly CONFLICTs on held items, N parallel agents that each run `pm next` will all be recommended the SAME top item, all try to claim it, and N-1 will bounce. The missing primitive is an atomic \"give me my own item\".\n\n## Design sketch\n`pm claim --next` (or `pm next --claim`): compute the pm next recommendation and claim it in one operation; on already_claimed_by conflict, retry with the next-ranked candidate (bounded, e.g. 10 candidates) until one claim succeeds; return the claimed item with the same rationale payload pm next emits. Honors --if-available semantics naturally (skip held candidates instead of erroring). Requires pm-8t5x semantics (deps: blocked_by) and benefits from pm-2muu's lock wait.\n\n## Definition of done\nN-parallel `pm claim --next` stress: N distinct items claimed, zero double-grants; recommendation rationale preserved in output; MCP action + contracts + completion + docs wired per the new-command checklist (grep replicate every site); spec covers conflict-retry and exhausted-candidates paths."
